HEADWORD: Despumation
<hw>Des`pu*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>despumatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>despumation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The
act of throwing up froth or scum; separation of the scum or impurities
from liquids; scumming; clarification.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

